00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:36,388 --> 00:01:40,197
[EP5: Lawyer Xu's Quiet Longing]

2
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:44,020
- Come down!
- Come catch me!

3
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,340
I'm sorry, miss.

4
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:59,275
Sorry,

5
00:01:59,275 --> 00:02:01,120
I didn't keep an eye on him.

6
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,661
It's okay.

7
00:02:11,544 --> 00:02:14,176
<i>I noticed that a lot of Cen Si Si's photos
on social media</i>

8
00:02:14,176 --> 00:02:16,096
<i>are imitating yours.</i>

9
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,980
What were you thinking?

10
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:44,960
Lawyer Xu,

11
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,458
thanks to your quick wit.

12
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:48,860
Otherwise, I would've been exposed.

13
00:02:50,212 --> 00:02:51,913
Nice performance.

14
00:02:53,090 --> 00:02:56,626
Adequate for a prime-time drama?

15
00:02:57,928 --> 00:02:59,907
Adequate to fool a layperson.

16
00:03:00,931 --> 00:03:03,100
<i>So he's a pro?</i>

17
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:05,680
<i>He'd think my acting...</i>

18
00:03:09,594 --> 00:03:10,691
Chen Hui,

19
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:12,276
drive Ms. Ruan

20
00:03:12,276 --> 00:03:14,520
and deliver a recording copy to Lawyer Liu.

21
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,560
I will.

22
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,656
Lawyer Xu, you're not returning to the firm?

23
00:03:17,656 --> 00:03:19,975
No, I'm heading to the airport.

24
00:03:20,576 --> 00:03:22,995
To the US immediately?

25
00:03:22,995 --> 00:03:24,800
Yes.

26
00:03:26,081 --> 00:03:27,916
So you're...

27
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:30,755
here about my case?

28
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:35,382
In Ms. Ruan's eyes,

29
00:03:35,382 --> 00:03:37,782
I'm such a loiterer?

30
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,240
Thank you anyway, Lawyer Xu,

31
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:47,352
for helping me collect evidence today.

32
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:48,854
You're so busy with work.

33
00:03:48,854 --> 00:03:50,630
Take care of yourself.

34
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:54,217
Safe ride.

35
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:10,043
<i>Senior,</i>

36
00:04:10,043 --> 00:04:11,793
<i>I lost my temper.</i>

37
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:13,837
<i>I didn't mean it.</i>

38
00:04:13,837 --> 00:04:16,013
<i>Actually, I didn't do them.</i>

39
00:04:16,013 --> 00:04:18,480
<i>Are you still around?</i>

40
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,209
<i>Realizing she had been recorded,</i>

41
00:04:20,209 --> 00:04:22,425
<i>she's trying to fix it.</i>

42
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:29,985
<i>It's not convenient. See you in court.</i>

43
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:49,392
[Three days later]

44
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:57,837
Coming!

45
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,799
Hello.

46
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,993
Hello, Mr. Xu.

47
00:05:01,993 --> 00:05:03,762
It's for you.

48
00:05:03,762 --> 00:05:05,138
Flowers for me?

49
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:06,932
It's the flowers that you bought.

50
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:10,252
And don't worry.
The payment has already been made.

51
00:05:11,439 --> 00:05:12,800
Can I help you move in?

52
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,859
Sorry, no.

53
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:18,318
What's the problem?

54
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:19,997
I just really don't need them.

55
00:05:19,997 --> 00:05:22,364
And do me a favor and throw them out.

56
00:05:22,364 --> 00:05:24,307
No need?

57
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:27,884
Thank you.

58
00:05:27,884 --> 00:05:28,954
Okay.

59
00:05:28,954 --> 00:05:31,231
- Bye.
- Bye-bye.

60
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:41,960
<i>♫ Boss, phone call ♫</i>

61
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,051
Hello?

62
00:05:43,051 --> 00:05:46,346
I told you my address,
not so that you could send this stuff.

63
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:47,743
What stuff?

64
00:05:47,743 --> 00:05:50,044
A pot of ugly flowers.

65
00:05:51,435 --> 00:05:52,936
Ugly?

66
00:05:52,936 --> 00:05:55,280
<i>Ruan Yu bought it to thank you.</i>

67
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:58,973
<i>Isn't it nice to liven up your house?</i>

68
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:01,820
Besides...

69
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:06,027
Sir! Excuse me.

70
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:10,412
I'm sorry.
Can you bring the flowers back to me?

71
00:06:10,412 --> 00:06:12,152
Why?

72
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,700
Thank you.

73
00:06:18,170 --> 00:06:19,946
Okay, no why.

74
00:06:19,946 --> 00:06:21,765
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

75
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:28,260
Didn't you thank Xu Huai Song for such a favor?

76
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:30,199
Of course, I did.

77
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,645
Look,

78
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:38,089
I sent him flowers, and he received.

79
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:39,839
I knew it.

80
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:42,611
Romance novelists really know
how to be romantic.

81
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:44,279
What did you send?

82
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:48,575
Cappuccino roses or Blue Enchantress?

83
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:50,300
Carola roses are nice, too.

84
00:06:51,370 --> 00:06:53,071
Kalanchoe.

85
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:56,720
It clears heat and detoxifies,
calms and refreshes the mind,

86
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,959
and helps with sleep.

87
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:00,170
He takes international flights frequently.

88
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:03,016
It's perfect for him with jet lag.

89
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,385
A practical gift?

90
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:09,512
Good idea.

91
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:12,999
So, did you only give one to him?

92
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:16,560
Careful. Easy, easy.

93
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,920
It's fine. It's not heavy.

94
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,480
- Where, Mao?
- There.

95
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,560
- In the corner.
- That corner?

96
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,539
What about the former one?

97
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,760
<i>Thank you.</i>

98
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,982
<i>You're welcome, Lawyer Xu.</i>

99
00:07:42,128 --> 00:07:44,310
<i>I'm organizing the rest documents.</i>

100
00:07:44,310 --> 00:07:46,859
<i>I might bother you again.</i>

101
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:50,661
<i>No need to be so polite.</i>

102
00:08:00,314 --> 00:08:02,108
<i>Yes.</i>

103
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:14,800
Evil Polar Fleece wants me to go to the office.

104
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,024
What a freak.

105
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:24,121
<i>Thank you, Ms. Ruan, for the money tree.</i>

106
00:08:30,636 --> 00:08:34,033
<i>What did you mean by "Besides"?</i>

107
00:08:35,413 --> 00:08:40,260
<i>I meant, besides you,
the whole firm received her gifts.</i>

108
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,559
Terminate the contract?

109
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:27,919
You mean we'll terminate the contract

110
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:29,480
for Wen Xiang's new book?

111
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,654
Do you know how many netizens

112
00:09:31,654 --> 00:09:34,073
attack us on our official Weibo?

113
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:37,840
They say we're publishing
plagiarized work shamelessly.

114
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:40,440
We've clarified the plagiarism dispute,
haven't we?

115
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,759
Poet clarified it herself.

116
00:09:42,759 --> 00:09:44,720
The rest is manipulated by Su Cheng.

117
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,169
She's slandering Wen Xiang.

118
00:09:46,169 --> 00:09:47,837
Facing a public outcry,

119
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:49,000
does the truth matter?

120
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,298
It certainly does!

121
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:52,340
If not, then why do we have laws?

122
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:54,679
The public outcry is incited by Su Cheng,

123
00:09:54,679 --> 00:09:56,440
whom Wen Xiang is suing.

124
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,960
The netizens will know the truth soon.

125
00:09:57,960 --> 00:10:01,000
Anyway, if the plagiarism dispute

126
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,353
doesn't settle in three days,

127
00:10:03,353 --> 00:10:06,600
we'll definitely terminate
all her publishing deals.

128
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,080
Terminating her contract now

129
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:10,240
means we support Su Cheng, which--

130
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:12,419
That's enough!

131
00:10:13,155 --> 00:10:14,323
I know

132
00:10:14,323 --> 00:10:17,201
you favor your classmate.

133
00:10:17,201 --> 00:10:18,620
But remember

134
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:20,328
your salary is paid by Liwen

135
00:10:20,328 --> 00:10:22,272
rather than Wen Xiang.

136
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:29,462
Speaking of salary,

137
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:31,799
when I joined Liwen,

138
00:10:31,799 --> 00:10:35,135
it gave me no resources.

139
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,637
Any promising author I scouted

140
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:40,206
would be poached by other editors.

141
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,519
It was Wen Xiang

142
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:46,977
who gave me her promising novels

143
00:10:46,977 --> 00:10:49,775
and trusted me 100%.

144
00:10:49,775 --> 00:10:51,546
She is my friend,

145
00:10:51,546 --> 00:10:53,194
my classmate,

146
00:10:53,194 --> 00:10:54,559
and more importantly,

147
00:10:54,559 --> 00:10:56,990
my best partner in my career.

148
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:58,240
Were it not for her,

149
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,620
I wouldn't have survived in this industry.

150
00:11:02,621 --> 00:11:04,998
If I remember correctly,

151
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:08,940
you also owe this position to her.

152
00:11:12,559 --> 00:11:15,400
If we can't tell right from wrong,
and kick down the ladder,

153
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,839
none will dare to work with us.

154
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:20,806
Shen Ming Ying.

155
00:11:20,806 --> 00:11:23,453
You'd better watch your words.

156
00:11:23,453 --> 00:11:26,352
Don't make yourself a target.

157
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:29,565
If the target can shield Wen Xiang,

158
00:11:29,565 --> 00:11:31,426
I'll be it

159
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:34,932
for sure.

160
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,279
<i>In court, the recording can only</i>

161
00:11:54,279 --> 00:11:55,679
<i>serve as supplementary evidence.</i>

162
00:11:55,679 --> 00:11:57,800
<i>But the counter-plagiarism comparison chart</i>

163
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,679
<i>can prove your novel's originality.</i>

164
00:12:00,679 --> 00:12:03,765
<i>Finish this up.</i>

165
00:12:03,765 --> 00:12:05,384
<i>Okay.</i>

166
00:12:50,759 --> 00:12:51,799
Lawyer Xu.

167
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:53,720
I have no more questions for Chapter 13.

168
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,859
I'll organize it tonight.

169
00:12:55,859 --> 00:12:57,683
<i>Yes.</i>

170
00:12:59,905 --> 00:13:01,886
Excuse me, I need to take this.

171
00:13:02,991 --> 00:13:04,490
<i>Hello?</i>

172
00:13:05,536 --> 00:13:07,115
I'm home.

173
00:13:08,872 --> 00:13:11,208
Might be the defendant's retaliation.

174
00:13:11,208 --> 00:13:13,836
<i>The higher-ups at SG are clear that</i>

175
00:13:13,836 --> 00:13:17,297
the defendant is capable
of remote bomb control.

176
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:26,389
Yes.

177
00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:28,500
That's a matter for the police.

178
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:31,809
<i>Okay, you guys handle it.</i>

179
00:13:37,109 --> 00:13:38,609
Sorry.

180
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:42,120
Lawyer Xu,

181
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:44,659
<i>isn't it getting late over there?</i>

182
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:50,179
<i>I drank coffee for nothing again?</i>

183
00:14:08,307 --> 00:14:10,247
What did you just say?

184
00:14:11,727 --> 00:14:13,759
I said, "Isn't it getting late over there?"

185
00:14:13,759 --> 00:14:16,140
Is it convenient to talk?

186
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:20,539
Sure.

187
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:31,455
Let's move to...

188
00:14:31,455 --> 00:14:33,406
Chapter 14.

189
00:14:43,341 --> 00:14:45,296
Chapter 14,

190
00:14:45,296 --> 00:14:47,696
paragraph 3.

191
00:14:49,723 --> 00:14:53,080
<i>He originally disliked furry animals,</i>

192
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:55,720
<i>until the day he passed by the art museum</i>

193
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:59,274
<i>and saw her feed a stray cat in the grass.</i>

194
00:14:59,274 --> 00:15:00,376
<i>Sunshine,</i>

195
00:15:00,376 --> 00:15:01,692
<i>a breeze,</i>

196
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:03,029
<i>the green grass,</i>

197
00:15:03,029 --> 00:15:04,237
<i>the cat,</i>

198
00:15:04,237 --> 00:15:06,120
<i>and her.</i>

199
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:07,360
<i>All of them</i>

200
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:10,200
<i>formed an extremely tender landscape</i>

201
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,279
<i>in his heart.</i>

202
00:15:12,279 --> 00:15:13,496
<i>From then on,</i>

203
00:15:13,496 --> 00:15:15,915
<i>he loved what she loved,</i>

204
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:18,200
<i>followed her lead,</i>

205
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:21,463
<i>greeted every cat in their school,</i>

206
00:15:21,463 --> 00:15:23,399
<i>but never...</i>

207
00:15:23,399 --> 00:15:25,759
<i>greeted</i>

208
00:15:25,759 --> 00:15:27,159
<i>her.</i>

209
00:15:36,679 --> 00:15:38,855
<i>Xu Huai Song liked cats
from the very beginning.</i>

210
00:15:38,855 --> 00:15:42,050
<i>Why did I adapt it for romance?</i>

211
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:49,806
The two sentences are exactly the same,
word for word.

212
00:15:49,806 --> 00:15:50,909
Lawyer Xu,

213
00:15:50,909 --> 00:15:53,240
what do you think?

214
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:55,454
I notice some nuances.

215
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:58,584
Your hero loved what she loved,

216
00:15:58,584 --> 00:16:01,160
while the other party's hero didn't.

217
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:12,679
I see.

218
00:16:12,679 --> 00:16:15,850
The Poet's hero knew
the heroine would pass by the art museum,

219
00:16:15,850 --> 00:16:17,279
<i>and he orchestrated it.</i>

220
00:16:17,279 --> 00:16:19,860
So it's not that he loved what she loved.

221
00:16:21,385 --> 00:16:22,940
I was being biased.

222
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:26,052
I forgot she adapted
the hero into a calculating man.

223
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,720
Calculating...

224
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:31,539
is a derogatory term, right?

225
00:16:34,578 --> 00:16:35,703
No.

226
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:39,320
Lawyer Xu,
don't get me wrong, I'm not against him,

227
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:42,360
<i>but analyzing rationally and calmly.</i>

228
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:44,360
<i>Calculating...</i>

229
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:46,757
can be a neutral term.

230
00:16:46,757 --> 00:16:49,899
From the positive side, it means he's smart.

231
00:17:00,854 --> 00:17:02,200
Is the coffee hot?

232
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:05,108
<i>Wipe it off, Lawyer Xu!</i>

233
00:17:05,108 --> 00:17:06,567
It's not hot.

234
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,620
Come here.

235
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:13,216
Lawyer Xu,

236
00:17:13,216 --> 00:17:14,450
how old is it?

237
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:15,899
Is it fully vaccinated?

238
00:17:15,899 --> 00:17:17,578
Is it okay to bathe it?

239
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:19,206
It's had all its shots.

240
00:17:19,206 --> 00:17:21,746
It's about six months old.

241
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:24,713
Okay. Then bathe it.

242
00:17:24,713 --> 00:17:27,965
The coffee residue
might be harmful for the kitten.

243
00:17:27,965 --> 00:17:30,000
We can discuss the case later.

244
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,459
<i>Okay.</i>

245
00:17:37,848 --> 00:17:39,268
<i>How to bathe it?</i>

246
00:17:39,268 --> 00:17:40,928
You don't know?

247
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:45,751
Isn't it your cat?

248
00:17:48,318 --> 00:17:51,377
<i>Whose cat is it?</i>

249
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,540
How to bathe it?

250
00:17:56,410 --> 00:17:59,320
You need cat shampoo,

251
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:01,000
an absorbent towel,

252
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,581
and ideally a dryer.

253
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:05,599
<i>Then put the kitten in a tub or a sink.</i>

254
00:18:05,599 --> 00:18:07,960
Use warm water between 38 and 40℃.

255
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,659
<i>- Be careful...</i>
- Wait.

256
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,576
What should I do now?

257
00:18:25,576 --> 00:18:27,273
Adjust the water temperature first.

258
00:18:27,273 --> 00:18:29,640
Don't shower it directly later.

259
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:31,799
<i>Fill the tub with water first.</i>

260
00:18:31,799 --> 00:18:34,140
Keep the water level low.

261
00:18:37,599 --> 00:18:38,784
It might be scared.

262
00:18:38,784 --> 00:18:41,021
So be very gentle.

263
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:49,337
What should I do now?

264
00:18:49,337 --> 00:18:51,756
Hold the scruff of its neck
with your left hand.

265
00:18:51,756 --> 00:18:53,992
Try to be gentle.

266
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:02,664
And then?

267
00:19:02,664 --> 00:19:04,429
Then wet it slowly from the neck down

268
00:19:04,429 --> 00:19:06,079
<i>with your right hand,</i>

269
00:19:06,079 --> 00:19:08,140
<i>and apply the shampoo.</i>

270
00:19:09,559 --> 00:19:12,019
Be careful not to let it choke on water.

271
00:20:25,519 --> 00:20:27,140
Finished.

272
00:20:28,936 --> 00:20:29,960
Okay.

273
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:33,160
Lawyer Xu,
wipe it down with the absorbent towel

274
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:34,817
<i>before putting it into the dryer.</i>

275
00:20:34,817 --> 00:20:36,279
<i>Wipe it gently.</i>

276
00:20:36,279 --> 00:20:39,019
And mute the dryer.

277
00:21:38,465 --> 00:21:40,726
<i>So he likes cats, too.</i>

278
00:21:41,799 --> 00:21:43,300
<i>Nice.</i>

279
00:22:26,637 --> 00:22:29,720
Lawyer Xu. I'm still here.

280
00:22:36,773 --> 00:22:38,314
I forgot.

281
00:22:47,701 --> 00:22:49,401
I need to take a shower.

282
00:22:50,704 --> 00:22:53,040
Then, Lawyer Xu.

283
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:54,458
Then move me...

284
00:22:54,458 --> 00:22:56,943
No, you move the laptop.

285
00:22:56,943 --> 00:22:59,408
Can't you just end the video call?

286
00:22:59,408 --> 00:23:00,599
Oh yes.

287
00:23:00,599 --> 00:23:01,964
Yes.

288
00:23:01,964 --> 00:23:03,700
I...

289
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:09,960
Oh my god, a naked man!

290
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:12,240
You scared the life out of me!

291
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:14,632
Xu Huai Song?

292
00:23:14,632 --> 00:23:15,720
What?

293
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:17,479
What are you doing? What's going on?

294
00:23:17,479 --> 00:23:19,858
- I...
- Confess everything. Now!

295
00:23:19,858 --> 00:23:22,373
Confess what?

296
00:23:22,373 --> 00:23:24,920
His cat splashed coffee all over him.

297
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:27,359
He didn't know how to bathe it,

298
00:23:27,359 --> 00:23:29,400
so he got splashed with water too.

299
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:31,780
That's what you saw.

300
00:23:34,915 --> 00:23:36,458
No.

301
00:23:36,458 --> 00:23:38,559
Something's fishy.

302
00:23:38,559 --> 00:23:40,504
What is it?

303
00:23:40,504 --> 00:23:41,577
First,

304
00:23:41,577 --> 00:23:42,680
he has a cat.

305
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:44,715
Second, he doesn't know how to bathe it.

306
00:23:44,715 --> 00:23:46,677
So, who usually bathes the cat?

307
00:23:46,677 --> 00:23:48,846
You mean,

308
00:23:48,846 --> 00:23:51,105
someone else lives with him?

309
00:23:52,516 --> 00:23:54,933
His girlfriend?

310
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:57,480
Maybe he usually takes it to a pet shop.

311
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:59,936
But possibly you're right.

312
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:03,499
True.

313
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:06,440
He clearly has a dryer at home.

314
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:09,860
There must be someone who bathes the cat.

315
00:24:12,119 --> 00:24:13,880
Besides, he's not young anymore.

316
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:15,454
And he's so outstanding.

317
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:17,090
It'd be weird if he doesn't have one.

318
00:24:17,090 --> 00:24:19,359
Yes, back to business.

319
00:24:19,359 --> 00:24:20,799
Good news.

320
00:24:20,799 --> 00:24:23,880
Your website's official account
posted a statement,

321
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:29,880
confirming it wasn't the Poet's original work,

322
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:32,680
Su Cheng's claim was groundless,

323
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:37,799
and you were the innocent, original writer.

324
00:24:37,799 --> 00:24:40,140
I sent you the statement. Check it.

325
00:24:41,119 --> 00:24:43,240
I didn't notice it just now.

326
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:46,527
<i>Counsels, this is the investigative report
by Qianhe Net.</i>

327
00:24:46,527 --> 00:24:48,654
<i>Can it serve as supplementary evidence
in court?</i>

328
00:24:48,654 --> 00:24:51,966
You should have seen our chief editor's face.

329
00:24:51,966 --> 00:24:55,320
Yesterday, she was ranting like a machine gun.

330
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:56,360
But today?

331
00:24:56,360 --> 00:25:00,599
Seeing the report,
she did a complete 180 so fast!

332
00:25:00,599 --> 00:25:04,459
I guess only the adaptive
can get that position.

333
00:25:05,672 --> 00:25:08,298
You quarreled with her again?

334
00:25:08,298 --> 00:25:09,459
No.

335
00:25:09,459 --> 00:25:10,960
I just stood my ground.

336
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:13,340
And she lashed out in impotent rage.

337
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:15,973
Thanks for taking the bullet for me.

338
00:25:15,973 --> 00:25:18,024
It's fine. Just treat me to a meal.

339
00:25:18,024 --> 00:25:19,144
I'll treat you to many meals.

340
00:25:19,144 --> 00:25:20,544
Deal.

341
00:25:21,438 --> 00:25:22,762
<i>With this investigative report,</i>

342
00:25:22,762 --> 00:25:25,162
<i>the odds are in our favor.</i>

343
00:25:26,652 --> 00:25:30,072
But shamed publicly by the website,

344
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:33,400
she'll probably pay trolls
to spin the story again.

345
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,720
No big deal.

346
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,744
Since we can't shut them up,

347
00:25:36,744 --> 00:25:38,579
we'll just close our eyes.

348
00:25:38,579 --> 00:25:40,398
Out of sight, out of mind.

349
00:25:44,035 --> 00:25:46,119
[she'll probably pay trolls
to spin the story again.]

350
00:25:46,119 --> 00:25:47,820
<i>True.</i>

351
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:54,160
As soon as we close the curtain,

352
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:56,359
- Lawyer Liu revealed it.
<i>- A replacement?</i>

353
00:25:56,359 --> 00:25:57,559
<i>- They gave up Poet</i>
- Look.

354
00:25:57,559 --> 00:25:59,440
<i>and shamed Su Cheng to protect Wen Xiang.</i>

355
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:00,519
<i>What a trade-off!</i>

356
00:26:00,519 --> 00:26:02,359
<i>The cash cow is always favored!</i>

357
00:26:02,359 --> 00:26:04,880
<i>But I think Wen Xiang owes it to luck.</i>

358
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:06,119
<i>Su Cheng is clearly a better writer.</i>

359
00:26:06,119 --> 00:26:08,079
<i>Society needs a voice for justice.</i>

360
00:26:08,079 --> 00:26:09,839
<i>I side with Su Cheng unconditionally.</i>

361
00:26:09,839 --> 00:26:11,400
<i>Are you that free?</i>

362
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:13,400
<i>Not really.</i>

363
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:14,865
<i>Then rewrite this.</i>

364
00:26:14,865 --> 00:26:17,560
<i>Your statement isn't strong enough.</i>

365
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,696
<i>Don't I have any pride?</i>

366
00:26:20,696 --> 00:26:22,831
<i>You only get one chance for a statement.</i>

367
00:26:22,831 --> 00:26:24,383
<i>If it's not to the point,</i>

368
00:26:24,383 --> 00:26:26,160
<i>it's a total failure.</i>

369
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,838
<i>Is the client's interest more important,</i>

370
00:26:27,838 --> 00:26:30,599
<i>or is your pride?</i>

371
00:26:30,599 --> 00:26:32,380
<i>Put up or shut up!</i>

372
00:26:34,261 --> 00:26:37,000
<i>Lawyer Liu, I'm not joking.</i>

373
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,740
<i>Your work really isn't up to par.</i>

374
00:26:42,039 --> 00:26:43,839
<i>I did write it in a hurry.</i>

375
00:26:43,839 --> 00:26:45,640
<i>I was swamped with all these cases.</i>

376
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:49,100
<i>I didn't think twice
before sending the screenshots.</i>

377
00:27:01,370 --> 00:27:03,288
<i>The recording evidence is secured.</i>

378
00:27:03,288 --> 00:27:05,624
<i>We can now face the defendant head-on.</i>

379
00:27:05,624 --> 00:27:07,918
<i>The website's report is only the first step.</i>

380
00:27:07,918 --> 00:27:10,504
<i>A backlash in public opinion is normal.</i>

381
00:27:10,504 --> 00:27:11,588
<i>Don't worry about it.</i>

382
00:27:11,588 --> 00:27:13,632
<i>A lawyer's statement will follow.</i>

383
00:27:13,632 --> 00:27:14,675
<i>By the end of today,</i>

384
00:27:14,675 --> 00:27:16,970
<i>the tide of public opinion will turn.</i>

385
00:27:16,970 --> 00:27:20,640
Lawyer Liu really isn't that great.

386
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:22,976
He's so careless.

387
00:27:22,976 --> 00:27:26,839
When it comes to being reliable,
it has to be Lawyer Xu.

388
00:27:26,839 --> 00:27:29,160
But he seems to be already taken.

389
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:32,219
The tone of his messages
to you is way too formal.

390
00:27:35,197 --> 00:27:36,778
Well...

391
00:27:38,075 --> 00:27:41,328
Then I'll be formal, too.

392
00:27:41,328 --> 00:27:43,440
<i>Okay, Lawyer Xu.</i>

393
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:45,900
<i>Thank both of you for your hard work.</i>

394
00:27:53,215 --> 00:27:54,835
Received.

395
00:28:02,264 --> 00:28:06,685
Remember? Someone made snide remarks
about your serials,

396
00:28:06,685 --> 00:28:07,769
claiming that Su Cheng was

397
00:28:07,769 --> 00:28:09,479
a much better storyteller than you.

398
00:28:09,479 --> 00:28:11,356
You didn't care,

399
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,709
saying everyone has their own taste

400
00:28:13,709 --> 00:28:17,197
and readers are free to choose and comment.

401
00:28:17,197 --> 00:28:18,290
But now?

402
00:28:18,290 --> 00:28:19,880
It turns out it wasn't a real reader.

403
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:22,822
It might be Cen Si Si's alt account.

404
00:28:23,994 --> 00:28:25,414
Probably.

405
00:28:25,414 --> 00:28:27,915
How did you offend her back in college?

406
00:28:27,915 --> 00:28:31,126
She's been hounding
and troubling you for years.

407
00:28:31,126 --> 00:28:33,321
I wish I knew.

408
00:28:36,383 --> 00:28:38,243
You robbed her of scholarship?

409
00:28:39,799 --> 00:28:41,739
Or her recommendation spot?

410
00:28:43,390 --> 00:28:45,098
Or...

411
00:28:45,098 --> 00:28:46,806
her man?

412
00:28:46,806 --> 00:28:47,880
No.

413
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:50,060
You've been single since birth.

414
00:28:54,610 --> 00:28:56,570
Ming Ying.

415
00:28:56,570 --> 00:28:58,280
Do you think it has something

416
00:28:58,280 --> 00:29:00,440
to do with Li Shi Can?

417
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:04,240
The way she mentioned him at the mall that day,

418
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:06,413
sounded like an admirer.

419
00:29:06,413 --> 00:29:08,297
Yes.

420
00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:11,208
She targets and imitates you,

421
00:29:11,208 --> 00:29:13,820
because she regards you as a rival in love?

422
00:29:14,528 --> 00:29:16,922
But I don't feel that way about Li Shi Can.

423
00:29:16,922 --> 00:29:18,715
In her case,

424
00:29:18,715 --> 00:29:20,592
it's more like an imaginary enemy.

425
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:22,320
Precisely.

426
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:24,471
That day, Cen Si Si did bring up

427
00:29:24,471 --> 00:29:27,440
the three of us being in the Arts Department,

428
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,600
in a snide tone.

429
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:30,769
But it has been years.

430
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:32,562
She's still hung up on it?

431
00:29:32,562 --> 00:29:34,119
Exactly.

432
00:29:34,119 --> 00:29:36,068
We haven't seen him in ages.

433
00:29:36,068 --> 00:29:40,807
He's now a top-tier idol.

434
00:29:53,079 --> 00:29:54,710
<i>Hello, everyone. I'm Li Shi Can.</i>

435
00:29:54,710 --> 00:29:57,920
<i>Thank you for joining my livestream today.</i>

436
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,214
<i>The livestream just started,</i>

437
00:29:59,214 --> 00:30:02,259
<i>and we've already had
more than a million views.</i>

438
00:30:02,259 --> 00:30:05,586
Today's giveaway seems very appealing to you.

439
00:30:05,586 --> 00:30:09,891
Yes, we have giveaways for Can's fans today.

440
00:30:09,891 --> 00:30:12,894
<i>Play Truth or Dare with Shi Can.</i>

441
00:30:12,894 --> 00:30:16,000
<i>- Shi Can...</i>
- As a superstar, he's still accessible.

442
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,759
He even plays Truth or Dare with his fans.

443
00:30:17,759 --> 00:30:20,680
<i>Since you all want to see it,
let's play it together.</i>

444
00:30:20,680 --> 00:30:23,196
<i>Good. Do you dare to accept the challenge?</i>

445
00:30:23,196 --> 00:30:24,641
<i>Sure.</i>

446
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:27,993
The lawyer's statement is closely followed

447
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:30,372
by marketing accounts' apologetic statements.

448
00:30:30,372 --> 00:30:34,540
The trolls Cen Si Si hired all turn silent now.

449
00:30:37,119 --> 00:30:39,820
Xu Huai Song is quite impressive.

450
00:30:40,424 --> 00:30:42,960
Our chief editor even said today

451
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:44,720
that considering your good image now,

452
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:46,240
it's high time you updated your serial

453
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,519
and capitalized on the trend.

454
00:30:48,519 --> 00:30:50,820
She's playing both sides.

455
00:30:53,537 --> 00:30:54,560
Just eat.

456
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,021
<i>The rules are as follows:</i>

457
00:30:56,021 --> 00:31:01,079
<i>Comment what you'd like Shi Can to do.</i>

458
00:31:01,079 --> 00:31:02,319
<i>If it's accepted,</i>

459
00:31:02,319 --> 00:31:04,960
<i>Shi Can will not only do it,</i>

460
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:08,580
<i>but also give you a signed photo.</i>

461
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:11,759
All right, let's take a look.

462
00:31:11,759 --> 00:31:15,440
A fan named "Poetic and Picturesque" says,

463
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:17,519
"7 is your lucky number.

464
00:31:17,519 --> 00:31:21,319
Call the 7th number in your contacts

465
00:31:21,319 --> 00:31:24,480
and say, see you at the usual place

466
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,839
the day after tomorrow morning."

467
00:31:25,839 --> 00:31:27,427
That's a tough request.

468
00:31:27,427 --> 00:31:30,039
<i>But since a fan's request,</i>

469
00:31:30,039 --> 00:31:33,141
<i>Shi Can won't refuse, right?</i>

470
00:31:33,141 --> 00:31:36,680
Of course.
Today's motto is to grant every request.

471
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:38,179
Give me the phone.

472
00:31:39,013 --> 00:31:40,940
[Call Song and say it's your classmate.]

473
00:31:46,559 --> 00:31:48,740
Okay, let's hear

474
00:31:48,740 --> 00:31:51,227
[Contacts]
who is the lucky one.

475
00:31:55,119 --> 00:31:56,665
This game is exciting.

476
00:31:56,665 --> 00:31:58,333
If it were me, I'd call my mom.

477
00:31:58,333 --> 00:32:00,093
That way, nothing could go wrong.

478
00:32:00,093 --> 00:32:02,979
Yeah, clever girl.

479
00:32:17,521 --> 00:32:19,012
Me?

480
00:32:19,012 --> 00:32:20,691
I don't think so.

481
00:32:20,691 --> 00:32:23,066
It's not his name.

482
00:32:23,066 --> 00:32:25,502
Besides, Ruan definitely

483
00:32:25,502 --> 00:32:28,200
won't rank 7th in the contacts.

484
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:29,699
Yeah.

485
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:34,140
Accept it, and you'll know.

486
00:32:40,713 --> 00:32:41,850
Hello?

487
00:32:41,850 --> 00:32:43,342
Hello.

488
00:32:45,077 --> 00:32:46,131
Long time no see.

489
00:32:46,131 --> 00:32:47,993
It's Shi Can.

490
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,939
Long time no see.

491
00:33:00,939 --> 00:33:03,641
How have you been lately?

492
00:33:04,902 --> 00:33:06,522
Not bad.

493
00:33:07,279 --> 00:33:09,976
So, are you still living there?

494
00:33:11,865 --> 00:33:13,240
<i>I just came back from abroad</i>

495
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:14,995
<i>and wanted to catch up with you.</i>

496
00:33:14,995 --> 00:33:17,480
<i>So, the day after tomorrow morning,</i>

497
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:19,790
<i>see you at the usual place.</i>

498
00:33:19,790 --> 00:33:21,251
Okay.

499
00:33:21,251 --> 00:33:23,028
See you there. Bye.

500
00:33:26,173 --> 00:33:28,039
What a coincidence!

501
00:33:28,039 --> 00:33:30,320
When you need it, it comes.

502
00:33:30,320 --> 00:33:33,066
Meet him, and ask him about Cen Si Si.

503
00:33:34,181 --> 00:33:36,360
The comments blow up.

504
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:39,319
<i>Whose sweet voice?</i>

505
00:33:39,319 --> 00:33:41,895
<i>Can, you can't see her at the usual place!</i>

506
00:33:41,895 --> 00:33:43,480
<i>Who came up with that dare?</i>

507
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:45,640
<i>Come out so that we can
"take good care" of you.</i>

508
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:48,177
My troublemakers.

509
00:33:49,008 --> 00:33:50,062
Remember to remind me

510
00:33:50,062 --> 00:33:51,920
to apologize to her after the livestream.

511
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:55,306
Otherwise, it'd be bad if I stood her up.

512
00:33:56,319 --> 00:33:58,440
As honey-tongued as before.

513
00:33:58,440 --> 00:34:01,122
He cleared it up indirectly in no time,

514
00:34:01,122 --> 00:34:02,640
and pacified his fans.

515
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:03,902
Cool.

516
00:34:03,902 --> 00:34:07,266
So he meant it was just a game,
not an invitation?

517
00:34:08,079 --> 00:34:09,159
Fine.

518
00:34:09,159 --> 00:34:12,619
When he calls you, ask him about Cen Si Si.

519
00:34:13,639 --> 00:34:15,387
I don't think that's a good idea.

520
00:34:15,387 --> 00:34:17,931
We haven't been in touch for so long.

521
00:34:17,931 --> 00:34:21,103
It's awkward to ask about
that right off the bat.

522
00:34:21,103 --> 00:34:23,440
And he doesn't know my pen name.

523
00:34:23,440 --> 00:34:26,559
He must be unaware of the situation.

524
00:34:26,559 --> 00:34:28,880
Well, thank you for your hard work.

525
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:30,102
Thank you.

526
00:34:30,102 --> 00:34:31,190
Thank you.

527
00:34:31,190 --> 00:34:34,614
Shi Can has prepared milk tea
for everyone in the lounge.

528
00:34:34,614 --> 00:34:36,750
Thank you for your hard work today. Thank you.

529
00:34:36,750 --> 00:34:38,410
- Xiao Fei, lead the way.
- Okay.

530
00:34:38,410 --> 00:34:40,620
This way, please. I'll take you to the drinks.

531
00:34:40,620 --> 00:34:42,274
- Good job.
- Bye.

532
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:52,676
Shi Can.

533
00:34:52,676 --> 00:34:54,884
Take a quick 15-minute break.

534
00:34:54,884 --> 00:34:57,920
Then get changed for the next commercial event.

535
00:34:57,920 --> 00:34:59,320
Okay.

536
00:35:02,312 --> 00:35:03,393
It's over.

537
00:35:03,393 --> 00:35:05,589
Don't even ask. I'm exhausted.

538
00:35:55,239 --> 00:35:58,000
<i>Miss, this is for you.</i>

539
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:59,459
<i>For me?</i>

540
00:36:14,174 --> 00:36:17,760
[2016 Midsummer Night's Dream Art Performance]

541
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:26,220
<i>Shi Can, it's perfect.</i>

542
00:36:27,239 --> 00:36:28,740
<i>Thank you.</i>

543
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:58,960
<i>What's going on?</i>

544
00:36:58,960 --> 00:37:00,320
<i>Jing Jing was there.</i>

545
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:02,079
<i>Why did the director ask me</i>

546
00:37:02,079 --> 00:37:03,440
<i>to send the bouquet in her place?</i>

547
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:05,400
<i>Because he's gossipy.</i>

548
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,520
<i>When you were absent,</i>

549
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:07,960
<i>he said you,</i>

550
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:09,639
<i>a golden scriptwriter backstage,</i>

551
00:37:09,639 --> 00:37:11,280
<i>and Li Shi Can,</i>

552
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:13,840
<i>a male lead onstage,</i>

553
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:16,280
<i>can be a perfect match in our department.</i>

554
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:19,000
<i>You stared blankly at him just now.</i>

555
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:21,146
<i>So our director wanted to set you two up.</i>

556
00:37:21,146 --> 00:37:22,173
<i>No.</i>

557
00:37:22,173 --> 00:37:23,741
<i>- I was just...
- Alright.</i>

558
00:37:23,741 --> 00:37:25,637
<i>No need to explain to your best friend.</i>

559
00:37:25,637 --> 00:37:28,079
<i>As if I wouldn't know.</i>

560
00:37:28,079 --> 00:37:29,800
<i>The same scenery,</i>

561
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:32,719
<i>but a different person.</i>

562
00:37:32,719 --> 00:37:35,199
<i>While you were staring at Li Shi Can,</i>

563
00:37:35,199 --> 00:37:39,220
<i>you were reminiscing about Xu someone, right?</i>

564
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:06,245
[Wen Xiang's Weibo]

565
00:38:08,622 --> 00:38:12,026
[It's my personal experience...]

566
00:38:19,719 --> 00:38:21,579
Xu someone...

567
00:38:23,679 --> 00:38:25,939
is your hero, right?

568
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:51,440
<i>It's said that Su Cheng, Wen Xiang's junior,</i>

569
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:53,289
<i>targets her due to a real-life dispute.</i>

570
00:38:53,289 --> 00:38:56,079
<i>Waiting for the truth. @Wen Xiang.</i>

571
00:38:56,079 --> 00:38:59,800
<i>No wonder after Poet's clarification
and apology,</i>

572
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:01,039
<i>Su Cheng, a third party,</i>

573
00:39:01,039 --> 00:39:03,400
<i>still smeared Wen Xiang.</i>

574
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:05,519
<i>So it's a real-life dispute.</i>

575
00:39:05,519 --> 00:39:07,559
<i>Fridge horror.</i>

576
00:39:07,559 --> 00:39:09,360
<i>Which school is Su Cheng from? Dig deeper.</i>

577
00:39:09,360 --> 00:39:11,880
Why are they doxxing her?

578
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:13,320
<i>Don't become a pawn.</i>

579
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:16,062
<i>Can't you see this move
is from a professional PR team?</i>

580
00:39:16,062 --> 00:39:18,160
<i>Wen Xiang has someone backing her.</i>

581
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:20,108
Online matters should stay online.

582
00:39:20,108 --> 00:39:22,304
I would never do such a thing.

583
00:39:24,639 --> 00:39:26,079
<i>The tide is turning so fast.</i>

584
00:39:26,079 --> 00:39:28,380
<i>Doesn't anyone think it's fishy?</i>

585
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:36,780
<i>Lawyer Xu, have you browsed Weibo?</i>

586
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:44,740
<i>Lawyer Liu, have you browsed Weibo?</i>

587
00:39:45,639 --> 00:39:47,199
<i>I have.</i>

588
00:39:47,199 --> 00:39:49,800
<i>Did your firm do this?</i>

589
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:52,199
<i>No.</i>

590
00:39:52,199 --> 00:39:53,852
<i>Then who could it be?</i>

591
00:39:53,852 --> 00:39:55,119
<i>No idea.</i>

592
00:39:55,119 --> 00:40:00,079
<i>To fight fire with fire isn't our solution.</i>

593
00:40:00,079 --> 00:40:04,059
<i>However,
the defendant might think we were behind this.</i>

594
00:40:05,159 --> 00:40:07,840
<i>Senior, now I know you.</i>

595
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:10,491
<i>In that case,
don't blame me for not being nice.</i>

596
00:40:10,491 --> 00:40:13,688
<i>Let's see who can play dirtier.</i>

597
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:16,619
Have you ever been nice to me?

598
00:40:19,044 --> 00:40:21,700
<i>The exposure wasn't done by me or my lawyer.</i>

599
00:40:21,700 --> 00:40:26,693
[The message has been sent,
but rejected by the receiver.]

600
00:40:32,516 --> 00:40:35,119
<i>Might be the defendant's retaliation.</i>

601
00:40:35,119 --> 00:40:37,719
<i>The higher-ups at SG are clear that</i>

602
00:40:37,719 --> 00:40:41,059
<i>the defendant is capable
of remote bomb control.</i>

603
00:40:41,859 --> 00:40:44,880
<i>Public security is so good here.</i>

604
00:40:44,880 --> 00:40:47,719
<i>Even if Cen Si Si wants revenge,</i>

605
00:40:47,719 --> 00:40:50,459
<i>she can't do much.</i>

606
00:40:56,208 --> 00:40:59,960
That's an incredible legend.

607
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:03,044
Due to a groundless infringement accusation,

608
00:41:03,044 --> 00:41:04,880
SG was sued by its competitors.

609
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:07,131
The scandal resulted in
a plummeting stock price

610
00:41:07,131 --> 00:41:09,519
and a serious economic crisis.

611
00:41:09,519 --> 00:41:10,960
Xu Yin, a reputable lawyer

612
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:11,960
at the California bar,

613
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:13,519
accepted the case.

614
00:41:13,519 --> 00:41:15,360
But two days before the trial,

615
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:17,141
he suffered a sudden stroke.

616
00:41:17,141 --> 00:41:18,719
After being resuscitated,

617
00:41:18,719 --> 00:41:21,760
he was diagnosed with vascular dementia.

618
00:41:21,760 --> 00:41:24,960
[San Francisco, 2022]
<i>Xu is currently unconscious!</i>

619
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:27,340
[San Francisco, 2022]
<i>What should we do about our case?</i>

620
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:30,320
<i>This is the most critical time.</i>

621
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:33,235
<i>And someone needs to take responsibility.</i>

622
00:41:33,235 --> 00:41:34,280
<i>You understand?</i>

623
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:36,360
<i>If no one is responsible,</i>

624
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:39,391
<i>I will sue your firm!</i>

625
00:41:39,391 --> 00:41:40,400
<i>Just bear with me.</i>

626
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:42,499
<i>I don't want to bear with you!</i>

627
00:41:43,545 --> 00:41:45,480
<i>Mr. Lawrence.</i>

628
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:48,740
<i>Now I'm on it.</i>

629
00:41:50,079 --> 00:41:52,360
In the end, Xu Yin's son,

630
00:41:52,360 --> 00:41:54,559
Xu Huai Song, stepped forward.

631
00:41:54,559 --> 00:41:57,119
He claimed that he had learned from his father

632
00:41:57,119 --> 00:41:58,719
and followed the case throughout,

633
00:41:58,719 --> 00:42:00,101
thus could take charge.

634
00:42:00,101 --> 00:42:01,561
If the case dragged on any longer,

635
00:42:01,561 --> 00:42:03,688
the stock situation would only worsen.

636
00:42:03,688 --> 00:42:06,190
At the last minute,
the board chose Xu Huai Song.

637
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:07,859
They didn't have much hope.

638
00:42:07,859 --> 00:42:10,739
After all,
changing counsel last minute is a huge risk.

639
00:42:10,739 --> 00:42:12,908
But the result...

640
00:42:12,908 --> 00:42:15,032
SG won the lawsuit.

641
00:42:15,032 --> 00:42:17,199
Xu Huai Song single-handedly

642
00:42:17,199 --> 00:42:18,747
brought SG

643
00:42:18,747 --> 00:42:21,147
back to life.

644
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:07,180
<i>Almost.</i>

645
00:44:14,880 --> 00:44:16,119
<i>Be good.</i>

646
00:44:16,119 --> 00:44:17,655
<i>Stay with me a little longer.</i>

647
00:44:17,655 --> 00:44:20,719
<i>I promise I'll feed you for a month, okay?</i>

648
00:44:20,719 --> 00:44:22,260
<i>Stay with me for a while.</i>

649
00:44:23,480 --> 00:44:27,280
<i>Look, a token of my sincerity.</i>

650
00:44:27,280 --> 00:44:28,939
<i>Stay with me a little longer.</i>

651
00:44:31,079 --> 00:44:32,159
<i>She's coming, she's coming.</i>

652
00:44:32,159 --> 00:44:34,380
<i>I'll give you a bit more. Here.</i>

653
00:44:39,199 --> 00:44:40,599
<i>Be good.</i>

654
00:44:50,107 --> 00:44:51,753
<i>I don't like cats.</i>

655
00:44:51,753 --> 00:44:53,572
<i>I like you.</i>

